SIMPLE: thrifty
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thrifty
<hw>Thrift"y</hw> <pr>(thr⟦icr⟧ft"⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos> <adjf>Thriftier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>;
<pos>superl.</pos> <adjf>Thriftiest</adjf>.]</amorph> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Given to, or evincing, thrift; characterized by economy and good
menegement of property; sparing; frugal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Her chaffer was so <qex>thrifty</qex> and so new.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I am glad he hath so much youth and vigor left, of which he hath
not been <qex>thrifty</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Thriving by industry and frugality; prosperous in
the acquisition of worldly goods; increasing in wealth; <as>as, a
<ex>thrifty</ex> farmer or mechanic</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Growing rapidly or vigorously; thriving; <as>as, a
<ex>thrifty</ex> plant or colt</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Secured by thrift; well husbanded.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I have five hundred crowns,⟦br⟧
The <qex>thrifty</qex> hire I saved under your father.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Well appearing; looking or being in good condition;
becoming.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I sit at home, I have no <qex>thrifty</qex> cloth.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Frugal; sparing; economical; saving;
careful.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thrill</ent>⟦br⟧
